3.DB: Add a failure-mode column to test failures
I
I/O Checkout Tool
Robin CooperCreated by: Robin Cooper
Created At: January 7th, 2026 8:53 PM
Description

The purpose of this column is to allow testers to describe how a test failed, so it should be a column in whichever table stores test failures / test history. The values should be joinable with the diagnostics table created in this issue, so they should be multiple choice once we add them to UI.

Should be text. Can be nullable. A null value represents no reason provided and should only be used for legacy data. Users shouldn't be able to submit new failures without a reason, but null will still be valid in the database.

Because we won't think of every possible way a test can fail, users can choose the value "Other" when none of the other reasons make sense. They'll be required to provide a comment in this situation.

Not sure whether we should add a check constraint to the column. I'm leaning towards no. If the value can't key into the table, we will just need to implement error handling UI to handle that situation. Not in scope for this task.


