6.DB: Add a network dependency graph to IO table
I
I/O Checkout Tool
Robin CooperCreated by: Robin Cooper
Created At: January 7th, 2026 9:26 PM
Description

The short term goal for this data is to be able to create a breadcrumb-like UI of the path from the PLC to the current device. Design and add database tables needed.

    For now, Ethernet/IP Host (VFD/FIO) > Device > Tag is good enough. Let's not worry about DPMs and the DLR ring.

    For 24V tags, there should be a reference to the name of the device that hosts the port that the current device is plugged into (e.g. VFD, FIO).

    For tags on IO Link devices, it should be the device name itself (because we can check for the status of the IO Link device via code, in a future task). There should probably be a new table that links IO Link devices to their parent IP device (once again, VFD or FIO).

    A table of Ethernet devices names and their IP addresses and DPM ports would also be useful, but ports are out of scope of this issue.




